  <p>
    Let's revisit our sailing ship.
    We have a vector for the direction of the mast M, going straight up (0,1,0),
    and the direction of the north-north-east wind W (1,0,2),
    and we want to find the direction the sail S should stick out in order to best catch the wind.
    The sail has to be perpendicular to the mast,
    and also perpendicular to the wind.
    To solve this, we can use the cross product: S = M x W.
  </p>
  <p>
    The cross product of A(a1,a2,a3)) and B(b1,b2,b3)) is:
  </p>
  <p>
    (a2b3-a3b2, a3b1-a1b3, a1b2-a2b1) So now we can plug in our numbers and solve our problem:
  </p>
  <p>
    S = MxW = (0,1,0)x(1,0,2) = ([1*2-0*0], [0*1-0*2], [0*0-1*1]) = (2,0,-1)
  </p>
